HEADWORD: Figurine
<hw>Fi`gu`rine"</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
<ets>dim</ets>. <ets>of figure</ets>.]</ety> <def>A very small figure,
whether human or of an animal; especially, one in terra cotta or the
like; -- distinguished from <contr>statuette</contr>, which is applied
to small figures in bronze, marble, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figurist</ent>⟦br⟧
